<paragraph id="8BB336ABBB205E6163F166399C56609F" blockId="13.[189,342,1126,1152]" box="[189,342,1126,1152]" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">
<heading id="D0FB81C7BB205E6163F166399C56609F" bold="true" box="[189,342,1126,1152]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="130" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B978EAB9BB205E6163F166399C56609F" bold="true" box="[189,342,1126,1152]" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336ABBB205E6163F166C99EA060CD" blockId="13.[189,1399,1173,1235]" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">
Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54B78809BB205E61629E66C99F0560AF" box="[466,517,1174,1200]" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="13372A2EBB205E61613066CA9FC760B0" box="[636,711,1173,1199]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1242,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-327@12.[189,1398,1242,1784]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 8. Geographic distribution of three Neotropical Heliodinidae. Red rectangle on left indicates the location in South America of the area enlarged on right. Circle = type locality of Helioandesia tarregai gen. et sp. nov. in northern Chile. Triangles = distribution of Aetole demarcha (Meyrick, 1917), the geographically nearest heliodinid species to H. tarregai gen. et sp. nov. on the western slopes of the Andes, in Peru. Square = type locality of Lithariapteryx loriculata (Meyrick, 1932) on the eastern slopes of the Andes of Bolivia, the morphologically nearest species to H. tarregai gen. et sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4452237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4452237/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), near Zapahuira, Parinacota Province, at about 
<quantity id="4CF49B4EBB205E61665566CA987760AF" box="[1305,1399,1173,1200]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="13" pageNumber="130" unit="m" value="3400.0">3400 m</quantity>
elevation on the western slopes of the Andes of northern 
<collectingCountry id="F31B763BBB205E61601566E79E9C60CD" box="[857,924,1208,1234]" name="Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">Chile</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
